'''Karasawayama Shrine''' is a [[Beppyo shrine]] in Sano, [[Tochigi Prefecture|Tochigi]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=Karasawayama Shrine|url=https://www.visit-tochigi.com/plan-your-trip/things-to-do/1792/|access-date=2023-04-07|website=Visit Tochigi|language=en-US}}</ref> It is located on the former grounds of {{ill|Karasawa Castle|en}}.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Karasawayama Castle|url=https://jref.com/articles/karasawayama-castle.491/|access-date=2023-04-07|website=Japan Reference|language=en-GB|12=draft|12=draft}}</ref> The castle grounds including the shrine is a National historic site of Japan<ref name="Bunka">{{cite web|title=唐沢山城跡|url=https://bunka.nii.ac.jp/heritages/detail/232631|access-date=25 December 2019|work=Cultural Heritage Online|publisher=Agency for Cultural Affairs|language=ja}}</ref>

==Overview==

'''Karasawayama Shrine''' (唐沢山神社, Karasawayama Jinja) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located at the summit of Karasawayama in [[Sano City]], [[Tochigi Prefecture]]. It enshrines [[Fujiwara no Hidesato]]. The shrine's former rank under the [[modern system of ranked Shinto shrines]] was that of a [[Bekkaku Kanpeisha]].

== Overview ==
The enshrined deity, Fujiwara no Hidesato, also known as Tawara Tōta, was appointed as the regional governor of [[Shimotsuke Province]] and built Karasawayama Castle on Karasawayama. His descendants, the [[Sano clan]], made the castle their residence. Hidesato, renowned for subduing the rebellion led by [[Taira no Masakado]], was later honored as a loyal servant of the emperor. Efforts to establish a shrine to worship him began primarily by his descendants and former retainers of the Sano clan. The shrine was founded and consecration_year on the former site of Karasawayama Castle's main enclosure in [[1883]] (Meiji 16). In [[1890]] (Meiji 23), it was designated as a Bekkaku Kanpeisha.

A detached precinct of the shrine includes Hidesato's grave, located 2 km west in Shinyoshimizu-cho, Sano City.

== Cultural Properties ==
=== Important Cultural Properties ===
* Armor fittings (known as Hiraiya) - A collection<ref>{{Cite web|和書|url= http://www.tochigi-edu.ed.jp/center/bunkazai/bunkazai/list/109.htm |title=「甲冑金具 号避来矢」『とちぎの文化財』|publisher=栃木県|accessdate=2019-09-14 }}</ref>

=== Other Cultural Properties ===
* Dragon crest helmet (helmet associated with [[Sano Fusatsuna]], a city-designated cultural property)

